{"id":643,"parent_id":0,"book_id":8,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":643,"title":"Hypocrite","subtitle":"","short_title":"Hypocrite","uri":"/scriptures/bd/hypocrite","content":[["div",{"id":"t1","uri":"/scriptures/bd/hypocrite.t1","order":".000.1654"},[".title","Hypocrite"],["div",{"id":"p1","uri":"/scriptures/bd/hypocrite.p1","order":".000.1655"},"The word generally denotes one who pretends to be religious when he is not (though it is sometimes used to mean simply a bad man; see",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/job/8.13"},"Job 8:13"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/job/13.16"},"13:16"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/isa/9.17"},"Isa. 9:17"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/isa/33.14"},"33:14"],"). Hypocrisy was the besetting sin of the Pharisees and was severely condemned by the Lord (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/23.13-33"},"Matt. 23:13–33"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/mark/12.38-40"},"Mark 12:38–40"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/luke/11.37-44"},"Luke 11:37–44"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/luke/20.46-47"},"20:46–47"],")."]]],"refs":null}
